          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1674228718262-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Cover with the lid and put the dish in the oven for 1hr 15 min – this is your<strong> beef & mushroom ragù</strong></p><p>While the ragù is in the oven, boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel your <strong>potatoes</strong> and chop them into large, bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-1674228724607-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-1674228724607-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-1674228724607-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-1674228724607-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-1674228724607-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes </strong>to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender and once done, drain and return to the pot</p><p>Return the pot to a low heat with a knob of <strong>butter</strong>,<strong> </strong>a splash of <strong>milk</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>,<strong> </strong>then mash until smooth and set aside to reheat later - this is your mash</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-1674228733746-x200.jpg",
