          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-1674228733746-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut your <strong>red chilli[es]</strong> in half lengthways, deseed and chop finely, then peel and finely slice (don't chop!) the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>garlic</strong>, then chop your <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Slice your <strong>ciabatta[s] </strong>into 3 slices per person,<strong> </strong>then add to a baking tray and put the tray in the oven for 5-6 min or until lightly toasted</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>and a knob of <strong>butter </strong>over a medium heat</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-1674228856983-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-1674228856983-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-1674228856983-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-1674228856983-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-1674228856983-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>sliced garlic</strong> and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped parsley</strong> (save the rest for garnish!) and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, drain, then add your <strong>king prawns</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until cooked through – this is your <strong>garlic & chilli king prawns starter</strong></p><p>While the ragù is cooking, enjoy the <strong>garlic & chilli king prawns starter</strong> in a sharing dish with the <strong>toasted ciabatta</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-2-1674230145675-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-2-1674230145675-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-2-1674230145675-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-2-1674230145675-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-2-1674230145675-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the beef & mushroom ragù has had 1hr, add your <strong>Tenderstem broccoli</strong> to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>,<strong> </strong>a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and a splash of <strong>cold water</strong>, then put the tray in the oven for 8-10 min or until tender, golden and crisp</p><p>Once ready, remove the <strong>beef & mushroom ragù</strong> from the oven and leave to stand for a couple of min before serving</p><p>Return the <strong>mash</strong> to a low heat with a splash of <strong>milk</strong> and <strong>half</strong> your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>(save the rest for garnish!) and cook for 2 min or until the mash is warmed through</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-1674228896771-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-1674228896771-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-1674228896771-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-1674228896771-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-1674228896771-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> mash </strong>with the <strong>roasted Tenderstem broccoli </strong>to the side and spoon over the <strong>beef & mushroom ragù</strong></p><p>Sprinkle over the <strong>remaining parsley </strong>and<strong> grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
